Build ubuntu-focal sdcard for Radxa rockpi4b:

Input files: ../rootfs-ubuntu-focal/linaro-esp.img
             ../rootfs-ubuntu-focal/linaro-rootfs.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
sudo vi /mnt/etc/gdm3/custom.conf ( uncomment WaylandEnable=false )
sync
sudo umount /mnt
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to SBC
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo vi /etc/apt/sources.list ( replace with http://mirrors.ocf.berkeley.edu/ubuntu-ports )
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
sync
sudo reboot

ps aux | grep -i apt ( wait till all apt done except grep -i apt )
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
Disable power saving and screen saver.
ps aux | grep -i apt ( wait till all apt done except grep -i apt )
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi

sudo apt install python3-pip python3-setuptools mpv speedtest-cli glmark2-es2 ffmpeg pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure
glmark2-es2

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 1 as default )

Firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' hyUhEjtlDLA -o avemaria.mp4
mpv avemaria.mp4

sudo rfkill list
sudo rfkill unblock bluetooth
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
